I think we need to have the following tests:

- Unit tests for LastPrePrepareSeqNoRestoreHelper:
-- cover `can_restore` method:
--- check that can not restore if not primary
--- check that can not retore if viewNo is not equal
--- other checks (cover every if-else with a test)
-- cover `restore` method:
--- check that replica and node values are restored properly

- Integration tests:
1) Restart Backup Primary [parametrize for viewNo=0 and 1]: 
- send reqs
- restart backup primary
- make sure that it restored prepare_seq_no, ordered_seq_no and watermarks
- make sure backup can continue ordering
2) Restart all nodes [parametrize for viewNo=0 and 1]: 
- send reqs
- restart all nodes
- make sure that nothing is restored
- make sure backup can continue ordering
3) Restart backup primary with high watermark  [parametrize for viewNo=0 and 1]: 
- send a lot of reqs (more than stable checkpoint, so that watermarks are changed)
- restart backup primary
- make sure that it restored prepare_seq_no, ordered_seq_no and watermarks
- make sure backup can continue ordering
4) Negative case [parametrize for viewNo=0 and 1]: 
- send a lot of reqs (more than stable checkpoint, so that watermarks are changed)
- stop backup primary on Inst2
- do view change
- start the node
- make sure that nothing is restored
- make sure backup can continue ordering

@lovesh 
I'm not yet comfortable with the following things in the PR:
1) Devops changes (in `build-3rd-parties.sh`)
2) Not all changes of mode from 755 to 644 are fixed (see diff)
3) I'm not comfortable with having FEEs in Plenum. Please check with Product owners / Nathan. My concerns are not only because of political issues (which are quite real), but also why we need it in Plenum if the intention of plugins is to be able to add functionality without modification of existing code.
4) self._bls_bft_replica.process_pre_prepare(pre_prepare, sender) - needs to be called for master only

Approved, although there is still a FEEs field in one place. I'm not convinced that we need it here, but if having the field is fine from political point of view, then, taking into account the urgency we can merge as is and do refactoring later together with Request format improvements. 
A good thing that the code says to *ignore* the FEEs field, so this is quite safe.

@dhh1128 
Thanks.

(1) Yes, I agree. I think it would be great to find a term for this, because I think we will need to distinguish services in NODE txns between just Observers and gatekeepers. Can we call ring0 nodes 'protectors' or 'defenders'? So that we have VALIDATORs, DEFENDERs, and OBSERVERs?

(2) Yes, Gatekeepers and Validators always send (propagate) write requests to f+1 Nodes.
This is the Client who can contact one Node only. So, a client sends write request to one gatekeeper, and the gatekeeper propagates this write request to at least f+1 Validators waiting for a Reply with state proof that he sends back to the Client.

I think we can approve the request with the following conditions:
1) I have some concerns about how Plugins are going to be registered and applied.
I think this PR can be merged (because it contains some good re-factorings and extending the previous PR).
But we decided to create a design for Plugins, and send a PR with the Design.
After analysing and discussing the Design, we can either say that the current approach is OK, or enhance it in separate PRs. 
2) We will re-factor initialization of ledgers in a separate re-factoring task (https://jira.hyperledger.org/browse/INDY-1038)

Approved with the following follow-up:
- a specific demo plugin implementation and tests will be done in the next PR
- a possible thinking of decorator-based hooks will be done in next PRs
